Description:
1.2 Acres (approx.) of Peace and Privacy in the Heart of Cockatoo
Set well back off the road and only a short distance to central Cockatoo, this home offers a great opportunity to set yourself up for life. Privately positioned yet close to all facilities including schools and transport, this home stretches itself across 4725m2 of flat and usable land. The home consists of 3 robed bedrooms including master with ensuite and walk in robe, study, central living area and lovely timber kitchen with dishwasher. Outside boasts a studio or ‘mancave’ with 2 separate rooms. Enjoy summer evenings on the back verandah taking in the serenity. Additional features of this property include glass house, 3 garden sheds, wood heater and wall heating. Contact Mick Dolphin on 0429 684522, Meaghan Dolphin on 0422 578 114 or Amie Colbert on 0413 160 413 to arrange your inspection now. Due to strong market conditions please call before the open to confirm that it is still going ahead.

Description:
Lovely Character Home on Half an Acre!
For those looking for their first home this is a beauty! Affordable and stylishly updated yet retaining its original character feel all within walking distance to the gorgeous Hills town of Cockatoo, its shops, cafes and schools.
Set back off the road and accessed by the circular drive with centre weeping mulberry, you'll immediately be enchanted with the homes exterior and gardens. Comprising of 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, the Master with ample built in robes and as new ensuite with access to the entertaining deck so you can throw open the doors and welcome in the morning sun and fresh air. The further 2 bedrooms are a good size, with 1 having a door to the family bathroom creating an ensuite effect. For family living there is a formal lounge with mantle and a good sized family room with a split system for comfort. The as new kitchen is in contemporary in design and colour with stainless appliances, gas cooktop and overlooks the dining area which opens out to the sunny enclosed entertaining deck, the perfect place for the little ones to play in safety. Features include 10 foot ceilings, quality wool carpets, original double hung windows and mains gas ducted heating.
For vehicles there's a carport and single lockup garage (which also has an office) and the mainly flat backyard is fully fenced with 2 garden sheds and magnificent Powton tree to provide shade in the warmer months. This lovely home will not be on the market for long - so be quick to inspect.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!
Grant Day 0417 565 745 or Bethany Day 0438 844 968

Description:
Your Hills Lifestyle Awaits!
Thinking about a tree change for the family? Then this is the perfect home for you - a classic Hills style home with room enough for all. Situated within walking distance to Cockatoo sporting ground & transport this brick family home sits on just over 3 quarters of a sunny, private acre with Crown Land behind, so you're assured of your peace & privacy. Offering 4 bedrooms, the Master, which is located at the front of the home, features plenty of robes & a new ensuite, while there are 2 large, robed bedrooms off the family living area & a spacious 4th bedroom with ensuite access to the family bathroom off the rumpus room which has its own external entrance, ideal for the teenager or in-laws. There is a lovely modern kitchen, (with 900mm stainless gas/electric stove), which opens on the large dining area that flows on to the entertaining deck, providing perfect spaces for entertaining family & friends. Add to this 2 living areas, one with a beautiful bay window with garden views & ambient open fire & the rumpus with wood fire & air conditioner for added comfort. Features include mains gas ducted heating, air-conditioning, bamboo floating floors, timber dado panelling & soaring timber vaulted ceilings. Outside you'll find a double garage with remote door, wood shed, a second driveway providing access to the rear, 10 x solar panels, a separate verandah, plenty of parking space & very gently sloping, landscaped, fenced gardens. This home leaves you nothing to do but move in and enjoy your new lifestyle!

Description:
The Ultimate Family Lifestyle On 1/2 An Acre!
Perfectly located in a peaceful and private location in the beautiful hills town of Cockatoo is this stunning country style family home. Boasting a flexible floor plan that is designed around everyone having their own space, the home features a large lounge room complete with Coonara and air conditioning. The large second living area/rumpus room is at the other end of the home, and there are 4 generously sized bedrooms, all with built in robes and the master that offers a full ensuite and walk in robe. The kitchen is central to the home and is feature packed with glass splash-backs, dishwasher, breakfast bar, quality appliances, timber benches, an enormous walk in pantry and adjoining meals area. Special features include a fresh modern color scheme, quality carpets, vaulted ceiling, split system heating and cooling, 2 wood heaters, gas ducted heating, and large windows that allow plenty of natural light to flow through the home. Entertain your friends and family in style all year round on the covered entertaining area, in complete privacy with spectacular views of the Warburton Ranges – there is also a built in bar with sink which is perfect for summer BBQ’s or parties! All of this sits proudly on 1/2 an acre of manicured gardens surrounding the home plus workshop, kids cubby house, ample storage, double carport and sealed driveway. This home is a must see!

Description:
16 ACRES WITH MAGNIFICENT VIEWS!!
Minutes from the Cockatoo township, in a beautiful part of the world, this fertile 16 acres of useable, fully fenced pasture is ready, complete with site cut, for you to start building the dream (STCA). Consisting of 3 paddocks, with 2 road frontages, north east views & a 25 mega litre water licence, this property is suitable for a myriad of uses, including an orchard, vineyard, nursery, grazing of livestock, horses, agistment or purely lifestyle. There is currently an older style 2 bedroom cottage on the property as well as a huge colourbond shed (6.5 X 20) with 3 phase power available, 5 kw solar panels & concrete aprons either side perfect to house all your machinery. Acreage of this size & quality are becoming rare in the Dandenong Ranges especially those with picturesque views & such a gentle slope. Call to arrange a private inspection of this magnificent parcel of land & start dreaming today!

Description:
Stunning Home, Majestic Views & Almost 8 Acres
With views that seem to go forever, this character filled home has been built with an obvious passion for rustic charm and architectural design. Set on approx. 8 acres the property offers the perfect mix of pasture and bush as well as a large landscaped cottage garden with plenty of secluded sitting nooks. The solid brick home itself has been lovingly built, and lined using hand-picked recycled timbers. The home offers 3 bedrooms, including a huge light filled master bedroom with ensuite, timber country-style kitchen, a large open plan lounge and dining with coonara, as well as a separate study area and a spacious bathroom which completes the picture-perfect home. Other features include double glazed windows throughout, double garage and split system air conditioning. Outside offers an additional double garage, two fully fenced paddocks with horse shelters and automatic water, a thriving fruit orchard, chicken pen, a massive veggie patch, and an extensive entertaining area that is the perfect place to sit back and take in the incredible view. All this is located on a sealed road with plenty of parking and is only 50 minutes from Melbourne and is close to everything that Emerald has to offer. This is the perfect place for relaxation in total solitude - start living your dream here today!
Due to strong market conditions please call before the open to confirm that the property is still available for sale.

Description:
Idyllic Family Home with Inground Pool
This lovely tumbled brick rancher within walking distance to village shops and public transport has been designed with family in mind.
This is a spacious home with heart both inside and out. A warm, earthy Australiana atmosphere and fully landscaped garden will bring enjoyment year round. Offering 4 bedrooms, including a parent's retreat main with ensuite and WIR, home office with leadlight bi-fold doors, 2 large living areas for family get-togethers, and a gorgeous kitchen with bench seating and all the mod cons. The new cooktop, wall oven, dishwasher, tiles and carpet complement the fresh paint and mean the new owners can move right in and enjoy.
Outside is also a true delight. The approach to the home is along a sealed and landscaped drive and arrives at the double garage and plenty of extra parking. Take a step out to the fantastic rear patio, perfect for entertaining, and enjoy a dip in the solar heated, in-ground pool. The tiered garden areas, mature trees, and leafy outlook surround the home and provide a peaceful and private sanctuary.
A 2kw solar system and 2,000L water tank support the home and help keep the budget in check.
Additional highlights include lovely leadlight features, wood fire, A/C, large chook pen and wood shed.
A truly idyllic home for any family. Make it yours today.

Description:
1 ACRE with GREAT VIEWS
Exceptional ACRE, GREAT VIEWS, STONE COTTAGE & more !
Owners would like to move on .
Sitting above the tree line is this 10 year old federation style home with mains GAS, WATER, SEWER, underground 3 phase power & uninterrupted views of the opposite ridge. Too many features to list, this is a must see . All the hard work has been done on this fully fenced one acre block . Fully landscaped with lawns & gardens with ample areas to enjoy the shade of established trees or simply take in the abundant bird life. Plenty of room for the kids to play , explore or pinch fruit from the trees in complete safety.
This home has polished floors throughout ( no carpets & non smokers) whilst the windows take advantage of the views. The main lounge can be closed off from the other areas whilst the kitchen, dining, family (with double French doors leading out to the deck), study and rumpus rooms are open plan. The 5.5m x 4m rumpus room is currently serving as an office. This could easily be made into another main bedroom with direct access to the front deck & views via sliding doors.
The main bedroom with walk in robe & full double shower en-suite is at one end of the house whilst the three bedrooms, with built in robes & shelves are at the other. These minor bedrooms share a bathroom and separate toilet. The kitchen has tiled floor, stainless steel splashback & stainless steel appliances, (double oven with 5 burner cooktop, dishwasher).
Ceiling fans & mains gas ducted heating throughout. Mains gas, mains water, mains sewage, underground comms & underground three phase power. The acre of gardens encompasses a paved dining area supported by two outside cooking areas, numerous fruit trees, native & exotic plants with 20000 ltr water tanks & pump to irrigate fruit trees & garden.
The main feature of the garden is a GRAND stone cottage complete with Sandstone floor, 2.5m arched windows, arched barn doors, open fire place & bar all connected to mains power & water. Potential earnings from B&B or additional bedroom.
The 10.5m x 6m shed at the bottom of the property with concrete floor, toilet, sink & steel work benches has been used as a workshop for an earthmoving business so there is plenty of room for trucks either side of it. The property is serviced by a concrete driveway that leads to the house with concrete gutters & under ground drainage.
Short stroll to Cockatoo Primary school , Public transport & shops. Post office , Chemist, Cafes , Bank , Supermarket. (NEW IGA supermarket under construction). Puffing Billy line adjacent to the property.
*Mains power ,gas & sewer
*Walk-in robe
* Full double en-suite
*Polished boards
*Study
*Rumpus room
*Stone cottage
*4 Garage spaces
*10+ car spaces
*3phase power
*Outdoor entertaining areas
*Fully usable 1 acre
VERY QUIET . VERY PRIVATE.! Please click on email agent button to arrange inspection. PHOTO ID REQUIRED on inspection .

Description:
Affordable Hills Hideaway!
Your peace and privacy is assured with this home on quarter of an acre set back off the road with plenty of off street parking. The home comprises of three bedrooms, the master with large walk in robe and ensuite and through clever use of the pitched ceilings, two bedrooms have a mezzanine level for extra storage space.
Add to this the kitchen with gas cooking and ample cupboard storage and good sized meals area with access to the verandah to allow for balmy summer night breezes. The family room has timber floors and wood heater for chilly nights as well as a mains gas wall heater for added convenience and there's a handy study nook, again making clever use of floor space.
Outside you'll find plenty of off street parking, a great sized back yard with rear access if needed, large 9 x 4m shed with concrete floor, plus a garden shed and the yard is fully fenced for the kids to play in safety.
This home is waiting for new owners with the vision for improvements or simply live in it as it is; the choice is yours.

With an elevated outlook you have a view over the main street and the Village and being made of brick the home is solid and has a totally refurbished roof so maintenance is low. The well maintained home offers 3 bedrooms with built in robes, family bathroom with spa bath, as new kitchen with ample cupboard space, dishwasher and gas cooking. This property so close to everything you could need and is a great little starter or investment opportunity!

3 Bedrooms on a Peaceful Quarter Acre!
Walking distance to everything Cockatoo has to offer; schools, shops, cafes and transport, this is a great first home or investment opportunity. Situated on nearly quarter of an acre there is plenty of room for the family to grow. The split level home is elevated and overlooks crown land and features three spacious bedrooms. Each bedroom has built in robes, soft carpet underfoot and they are located adjacent to the central bathroom with separate toilet for convenience. The kitchen (with dishwasher and gas cooking), meals area and living are open plan and the living area is heated with a cosy wood heater which has a gate around it so the little ones are safe. Other features include a split system cooling and ceiling fan for comfort in the warmer months, polished floor in the kitchen and vaulted ceilings. The dining and living area also open out to the fantastic undercover entertaining deck; the perfect spot for entertaining friends and family whilst watching the kids playing in the yard below. Outdoor features include sunny open areas, garden shed, fencing and carport. If peace and privacy is what you're looking for then this home is for you and at this price it wont last long.
